<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3882] &quot;final&quot; not working as expected</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3882</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;neither final properties nor final fields are shielded from mutation if the mutator is a method in the same object.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Person {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; name = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;scott&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
    def foo() {
        name = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Dierk&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
    }
}
def p =  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Person()
p.foo()
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;assert&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Dierk&quot;&lt;/span&gt; != p.name

&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// credits: Scott Davis  &lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
