                            <comment id="14478750" author="paulk" created="Wed, 2 Dec 2009 07:48:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just as a comment, consider this example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;class Person {&lt;br/&gt;
    Person() &lt;/p&gt;
{ name = &apos;Jochen&apos; }
&lt;p&gt;    final String name = &apos;Scott&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
    def foo() &lt;/p&gt;
{
//        name = &apos;Dierk&apos;
    }
&lt;p&gt;}&lt;br/&gt;
def p =  new Person()&lt;br/&gt;
p.metaClass.foo = &lt;/p&gt;
{ -&amp;gt; delegate.@name = &apos;Guillaume&apos; }
&lt;p&gt;p.foo()&lt;br/&gt;
println p.name // =&amp;gt; &apos;Guillaume&apos;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If we uncomment out line 5, we get a compilation error even though the program would be fine at runtime - so we aren&apos;t being fully dynamic here - but being stricter here to honor JVM semantics around final.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
